A function defines a strict number of parameters, and if it is called with a different number of arguments it will throw an error.

frontmatter.shortDescription: Functions must be called with the same number of arguments as defined in their signature
frontmatter.shortCorrection: Functions can be called with a different number of arguments as defined in their signature
